<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="479" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,394,709]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,322,430,457]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The male of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Ozerov and Krivosheina" authorityYear="2015" box="[472,608,431,457]" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="richterae">
<emphasis box="[472,608,431,457]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">C. richterae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be recognized by subshining scutum, thoracic sclerites with grey microtrichose, yellow legs, and anterior lobe of surstylus which is slender and deeply curved posteriorly (
<figureCitation box="[1284,1367,467,493]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[287,1300,730,1332]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,730,1358]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Cordilura richterae Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina, specimen from Hokkaido. 21, male sternite V; 22, male terminalia, lateral view; 23, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701091/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Fig. 23</figureCitation>
). Scutum normally black, but with a pair of longitudinal dark stripes on yellow ground color in the pale (teneral) form.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,394,709]" box="[199,418,539,565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,286,539,565]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Female</emphasis>
. Unknown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
