<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="479" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="8.[151,1437,394,709]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,611,637]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Remarks.</emphasis>
According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G." box="[477,817,610,637]" pageId="8" pageNumber="479" pagination="489 - 493" refId="ref7309" refString="Ozerov, A. L. &amp; Krivosheina, M. G. (2015) Two new species of the genus Cordilura Fallen, 1810 (Diptera, Scathophagidae) from the Russian Far East. Zootaxa, 4040 (4), 489 - 493. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4040.4.11" type="journal article" year="2015">Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina (2015)</bibRefCitation>
, this species resembles 
<taxonomicName authority="Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina, 2012" authorityName="Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina" authorityYear="2012" class="Insecta" family="Muscidae" genus="Cordilura" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="479" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sidorenkoi">
<emphasis box="[1085,1235,611,637]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">C. sidorenkoi</emphasis>
Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina, 2012
</taxonomicName>
, but is distinguished from it by having black thorax, black coxae and tibiae in mid and hind legs, strong setae on male sternite V (
<figureCitation box="[434,516,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[287,1300,730,1332]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,730,1358]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Cordilura richterae Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina, specimen from Hokkaido. 21, male sternite V; 22, male terminalia, lateral view; 23, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701091/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Fig. 21</figureCitation>
) and posterior lobe of surstylus (
<figureCitation box="[885,1016,683,709]" captionStart="FIGURES 21–23" captionStartId="8.[151,264,1384,1409]" captionTargetBox="[287,1300,730,1332]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[241,1346,730,1358]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURES 21–23. Cordilura richterae Ozerov &amp; Krivosheina, specimen from Hokkaido. 21, male sternite V; 22, male terminalia, lateral view; 23, male terminalia, posterior view." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3701091" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3701091/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="479">Figs 22, 23</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
